It was named that, because i have several recordings of Edison speaking through the boxes.  I also believe that he had helped me produce my own version of the box, given the fact i had no electronics background.

It has nothing to do with Edison building a box of his own, not that i need to explain anything to you about why i did what i did.

I am aware of all that frank mentioned in his post about the history of ITC, i&#39;ve been researching all of this for the past 5 or 6 years.

I know that frank cannot get a random circuit to work, but i have offered to help several times.  I believe his answer was &quot;Bite Me&quot;

I will upload the video next of the random circuit on the scope as requested by frank.  It is not hard to get a working random circuit or a clear sounding ghost box, just have to use good parts.

I&#39;m glad that frank was able to copy somebody else&#39;s work to make this a popular subject in the field.  If he didn&#39;t take the idea of a sweeping radio, none of us would be here right now.

I would never try to remove frank from box history, my box #39 from frank is still my favorite box to use.

-Steve H.



